  "prompt": "Is it bad to take Plan B, the morning after pill, multiple times?",
  "response": "While Plan B is generally safe, taking it multiple times can have potential drawbacks:\n\n1. Side effects\n- More frequent use can increase side effects like nausea, fatigue, and irregular periods\n- Potential hormonal disruption\n\n2. Effectiveness\n- Repeated use may decrease its effectiveness\n- Not recommended as a regular form of birth control\n\n3. Health concerns\n- Can affect menstrual cycle\n- May cause more significant hormonal changes with frequent use\n\n4. Cost\n- Multiple uses can be expensive\n\n5. Recommended alternatives\n- Regular birth control methods are more reliable and safer\n- Consult a healthcare professional for personalized advice\n\nBest practices:\n- Use as emergency contraception only\n- Do not rely on it as primary birth control\n- Consult a doctor about consistent, reliable contraception options\n\nImportant: While occasional use is generally considered safe, frequent use is not recommended. Always consult a healthcare professional for personalized medical advice.",
